  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Reintegration for the Protection of Returnees in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project addresses the most urgent reintegration needs of Burundian returnees from Tanzania to address the potential security risks that often accompany such an influx of returnees and pose a potential threat to Burundi&apos;s stability, social cohesion activities, including quick impact projects (QIPs) and cash for work will be carried out. In addition, through the adoption of a participative community approach, protection concerns of the returnee population will be collected, information on rights and entitlements disseminated and appropriate referrals made to service providers.</narrative>
  </description>
